CoordinateTransformation
public class UnReferencedCoordinateTransformation
extends BaseCoordinateTransformation

The UnReferencedCoordinateTransformation class provides un-referenced conversions (not referenced to WGS84.aka no datum transformation) for the geometry package.

UnReferencedCoordinateTransformation

public UnReferencedCoordinateTransformation(CoordinateSystem source,
                                            CoordinateSystem target,
                                            Point3D shift)
Constructs an un-referenced coordinate transformation given a source and target coordinate system and a shift (datum). This allows one to calculate the datum shift for the middle of the screen and use it on the entire screen (As the datum shifts in comparison to the screen pixel accuracy/width cannot be seen by the naked eye). (An often overlooked performance consideration as there's no reason to calculate datum shifts for every coordinate pair)

Parameters:
source - the source referenced coordinate system
target - the target referenced coordinate system
shift - the datum shift to apply
